fields.title: Marca
fields.content: This is Spain's national daily sport newspaper owned by Unidad Editorial. The newspaper focuses primarily on football, in particular the day-to-day activities of Real Madrid, FC Barcelona, and Atlético Madrid.

fields.title: The New York Times
fields.content: This is a daily newspaper based in New York City with a worldwide readership reported in 2022 to comprise 740,000 paid print subscribers, and 8.6 million paid digital subscribers.

fields.title: THE WALL STREET JOURNAL
fields.content: The newspaper was founded at the end of the nineteenth century. The publication positions itself as a business newspaper and is dedicated primarily to American and international business and financial news.

fields.title: THE WASHINGTON POST
fields.content: The newspaper made a name for itself by reporting on side-effects of the White House, Congress, and the US federal government. The publication is one of the largest in the United States and the oldest.

fields.title: Vogue
fields.content: This is a women's fashion magazine published since 1892 by Condé Nast Publications. Published in many countries around the world.

fields.title: THE GUARDIAN
fields.content: The publication has been published in the UK since 1821 daily. Covers world news in various fields. According to political views, the Guardian is classified as left-liberal. It is believed that the editorial board of the newspaper is in fairly close relations with the British Labor Party.
